WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.429 --> 00:00:15.682 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI gasps] You want me
to take him to see Inari?

00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:19.436 position:50% align:center
Well, yeah, he's a new member,
so... go and say hello.

00:00:19.519 --> 00:00:23.314 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI groans] You know I
can't deal with that woman.

00:00:23.398 --> 00:00:24.649 position:50% align:center
Inari?

00:00:24.733 --> 00:00:26.818 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:00:26.901 --> 00:00:30.030 position:50% align:center
Inari Yoko. She's a
kitsune kemono,

00:00:30.113 --> 00:00:33.033 position:50% align:center
but she holds a powerful
position with the police.

00:00:33.116 --> 00:00:34.242 position:50% align:center
When you're a detective,

00:00:34.325 --> 00:00:36.619 position:50% align:center
you end up asking them
for lots of favors.

00:00:36.703 --> 00:00:38.621 position:50% align:center
I told her you would be coming.

00:00:38.705 --> 00:00:40.123 position:50% align:center
These two will show you the way.

00:00:40.206 --> 00:00:41.416 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA giggles]

00:00:41.499 --> 00:00:42.792 position:50% align:center
Listen up, kid.

00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:44.586 position:50% align:center
You and I might be
working together,

00:00:44.669 --> 00:00:46.546 position:50% align:center
but that doesn't
mean we're friends.

00:00:46.629 --> 00:00:48.423 position:50% align:center
Let's go! And guess what?

00:00:48.506 --> 00:00:50.008 position:50% align:center
Right near the police station,

00:00:50.091 --> 00:00:52.761 position:50% align:center
there happens to be the cutest
little café you've ever seen!

00:00:52.844 --> 00:00:55.388 position:50% align:center
--You'll love the latte art--
--[INUGAMI] Kabane.

00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:57.474 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:00:57.557 --> 00:00:59.684 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Take this with you.

00:00:59.768 --> 00:01:01.061 position:50% align:center
What is it?

00:01:01.144 --> 00:01:04.105 position:50% align:center
Um. Little good-luck
charm of sorts.

00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:08.360 position:50% align:center
[POLICEMEN] Welcome back,
Superintendent Inari!

00:01:08.443 --> 00:01:11.946 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Wow. Everyone's all lined up!

00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:14.574 position:50% align:center
Mornin' ma'am.
Thanks for all you do.

00:01:14.657 --> 00:01:16.534 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Oh, Chief, how sweet.

00:01:16.618 --> 00:01:19.454 position:50% align:center
You didn't have to come
and greet me personally!

00:01:19.537 --> 00:01:21.831 position:50% align:center
I can take your coat,
Superintendent.

00:01:21.915 --> 00:01:22.957 position:50% align:center
Here's your mirror, ma'am.

00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:24.542 position:50% align:center
Anything else you need?

00:01:24.626 --> 00:01:27.545 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Wow! Thank you, boys.

00:01:27.629 --> 00:01:31.591 position:50% align:center
Guess I'll have to give
you a reward, won't I?

00:01:31.675 --> 00:01:33.218 position:50% align:center
[INARI chuckles]

00:01:40.475 --> 00:01:42.018 position:50% align:center
Take a big sniff, boys.

00:01:42.102 --> 00:01:45.480 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you'll enjoy it.

00:01:45.563 --> 00:01:50.568 position:50% align:center
♪

00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:18.656 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
It's so crowded.

00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:20.200 position:50% align:center
I know, it's crazy!

00:03:20.283 --> 00:03:22.911 position:50% align:center
I was shocked the first time
I experienced it, too!

00:03:22.994 --> 00:03:24.537 position:50% align:center
--[SHIKI] Hey!
--[AKIRA] Huh?

00:03:24.621 --> 00:03:26.706 position:50% align:center
Try to keep up, will ya?

00:03:28.875 --> 00:03:30.794 position:50% align:center
Why're there so many people?

00:03:30.877 --> 00:03:32.879 position:50% align:center
Well, 'cause it's Tokyo.

00:03:33.963 --> 00:03:35.965 position:50% align:center
Don't any of them work, though?

00:03:36.049 --> 00:03:38.051 position:50% align:center
There are all sorts
of jobs in the city.

00:03:38.134 --> 00:03:39.803 position:50% align:center
Oh. Didn't know that.

00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:42.097 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA gasps]
Yay! Lookie lookie!

00:03:43.807 --> 00:03:45.684 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA] There's the place
that I was telling you about!

00:03:45.767 --> 00:03:46.726 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA giggles]

00:03:46.810 --> 00:03:48.812 position:50% align:center
Remember when I
told you to keep up?

00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.023 position:50% align:center
Is this it?

00:03:52.107 --> 00:03:55.318 position:50% align:center
Shinjuku Police Station.
Let's go.

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.404 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Mm? Wait up, guys!

00:03:59.739 --> 00:04:00.532 position:50% align:center
[MAN A]
Here, ma'am.

00:04:00.615 --> 00:04:01.783 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN C]
Thank you.

00:04:01.866 --> 00:04:04.536 position:50% align:center
Huh? Superintendent Inari?

00:04:04.619 --> 00:04:07.288 position:50% align:center
Listen, I don't know where you
get your information, kids,

00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:09.708 position:50% align:center
but the superintendent
is a busy woman.

00:04:09.791 --> 00:04:12.752 position:50% align:center
She doesn't have time to deal
with ragamuffins like you.

00:04:12.836 --> 00:04:14.212 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] I told you,
we have an appointment!

00:04:14.295 --> 00:04:15.380 position:50% align:center
What's the deal?

00:04:15.463 --> 00:04:17.757 position:50% align:center
I wasn't informed
about any appointment.

00:04:17.841 --> 00:04:20.343 position:50% align:center
Then go confirm it and
find out for yourself!

00:04:20.427 --> 00:04:22.846 position:50% align:center
Geez, just give it a rest, pal.

00:04:22.929 --> 00:04:24.597 position:50% align:center
I don't gotta do nothin'.

00:04:24.681 --> 00:04:26.683 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] Why should you get
to decide that, though?

00:04:26.766 --> 00:04:28.893 position:50% align:center
You'll never know the
answer until you ask!

00:04:30.228 --> 00:04:32.605 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Who's that? Some girl?

00:04:32.689 --> 00:04:34.274 position:50% align:center
Ah, Kon, what's up?

00:04:34.357 --> 00:04:36.818 position:50% align:center
You 'bout to run an errand
for Superintendent Inari?

00:04:36.901 --> 00:04:38.111 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI grunts]

00:04:39.195 --> 00:04:41.114 position:50% align:center
Which one's Kabane?

00:04:41.197 --> 00:04:42.282 position:50% align:center
That's my name.

00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:44.951 position:50% align:center
All right, Lady Inari
is asking for you.

00:04:45.035 --> 00:04:46.619 position:50% align:center
Come with me.

00:04:46.703 --> 00:04:47.454 position:50% align:center
What?

00:04:47.537 --> 00:04:50.749 position:50% align:center
Told ya, ya big dope.

00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:53.877 position:50% align:center
Hold it. The one she
wants to see is Kabane.

00:04:53.960 --> 00:04:55.253 position:50% align:center
Not you other two.

00:04:55.337 --> 00:04:56.963 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI groans]

00:04:57.047 --> 00:04:57.964 position:50% align:center
Be right back.

00:04:58.048 --> 00:05:00.967 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI gasps]
Hey! Wait up!

00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:05.305 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI growls] What the hell
is that girl's problem?

00:05:05.388 --> 00:05:06.806 position:50% align:center
[MALE RECEPTIONIST A chuckles]

00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:17.942 position:50% align:center
[bell rings]

00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:29.829 position:50% align:center
[KON]
We're here.

00:05:29.913 --> 00:05:31.247 position:50% align:center
Go inside.

00:05:32.707 --> 00:05:34.125 position:50% align:center
[KABANE grunts]

00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:37.671 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Welcome!

00:05:37.754 --> 00:05:38.963 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Hm?

00:05:39.923 --> 00:05:42.634 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:05:42.717 --> 00:05:44.594 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Hello there. Uh...

00:05:44.678 --> 00:05:46.721 position:50% align:center
My name is Inari.

00:05:46.805 --> 00:05:49.933 position:50% align:center
Superintendent of the
Metropolitan Police.

00:05:50.975 --> 00:05:52.811 position:50% align:center
Thanks for having me.

00:05:52.894 --> 00:05:54.396 position:50% align:center
The pleasure is all mine.

00:05:54.479 --> 00:05:55.855 position:50% align:center
Please have a seat.

00:05:55.939 --> 00:05:57.816 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Okay.

00:05:57.899 --> 00:06:00.193 position:50% align:center
[INARI] I've been wanting
to meet you, Kabane.

00:06:00.276 --> 00:06:04.447 position:50% align:center
I've already heard so much
about you from Inugami.

00:06:04.531 --> 00:06:07.742 position:50% align:center
Things like how you're a
khoular-and-a-human hanyo,

00:06:07.826 --> 00:06:10.078 position:50% align:center
and how you were taken
in by your aunt when you 

00:06:10.161 --> 00:06:13.456 position:50% align:center
were a baby, together with
your lifestone, right?

00:06:13.540 --> 00:06:14.582 position:50% align:center
Yes, ma'am.

00:06:14.666 --> 00:06:16.751 position:50% align:center
Amazing!

00:06:16.835 --> 00:06:18.294 position:50% align:center
Lifestones are super-rare,

00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:20.797 position:50% align:center
I don't know if you
were aware of that fact.

00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:24.843 position:50% align:center
But oh, gosh. I sure
would love to see it!

00:06:24.926 --> 00:06:28.930 position:50% align:center
I can only imagine what
it must look like!

00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:31.266 position:50% align:center
I can show you it.

00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:32.434 position:50% align:center
Ta-da.

00:06:32.517 --> 00:06:35.520 position:50% align:center
Aw, I can't get a
good look from here.

00:06:35.603 --> 00:06:39.274 position:50% align:center
Would you mind bringing
it a bit closer?

00:06:39.357 --> 00:06:40.775 position:50% align:center
Yeah, no problem.

00:06:41.943 --> 00:06:46.781 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Incredible! Very nice!

00:06:46.865 --> 00:06:49.826 position:50% align:center
It definitely looks super-rare!

00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:53.246 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Tell me.

00:06:53.329 --> 00:06:56.374 position:50% align:center
Do you happen to know
what this stone is?

00:06:56.458 --> 00:06:58.418 position:50% align:center
Something that
prevents my thirst.

00:06:58.501 --> 00:06:59.794 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Correct!

00:06:59.878 --> 00:07:02.797 position:50% align:center
As kemono, we absorb energy.

00:07:02.881 --> 00:07:06.301 position:50% align:center
Mental. Physical.
Emotional. Sensory.

00:07:06.384 --> 00:07:09.262 position:50% align:center
And whatever other
types humans produce.

00:07:09.346 --> 00:07:11.931 position:50% align:center
So that we may
sustain ourselves.

00:07:12.015 --> 00:07:15.477 position:50% align:center
Inugami and I haven't always
gotten along so well.

00:07:15.560 --> 00:07:17.354 position:50% align:center
But when it comes down to it,

00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:20.273 position:50% align:center
I'm one side of the coin
and he is the other.

00:07:20.357 --> 00:07:24.611 position:50% align:center
So, in order to assist humans
for the sake of kemono-kind,

00:07:24.694 --> 00:07:26.905 position:50% align:center
we've ended up playing nice.

00:07:26.988 --> 00:07:28.865 position:50% align:center
But you know what, Kabane?

00:07:28.948 --> 00:07:30.325 position:50% align:center
Now that you've
made an appearance,

00:07:30.408 --> 00:07:32.869 position:50% align:center
the situation is
a bit different.

00:07:32.952 --> 00:07:34.871 position:50% align:center
Your lifestone's used
to prevent thirst,

00:07:34.954 --> 00:07:36.956 position:50% align:center
but do you know
what that means?

00:07:38.750 --> 00:07:39.876 position:50% align:center
If we have one of these,

00:07:39.959 --> 00:07:42.003 position:50% align:center
we won't need humans
to feed off of.

00:07:42.087 --> 00:07:44.214 position:50% align:center
And wouldn't that
just be wonderful?

00:07:51.346 --> 00:07:52.806 position:50% align:center
Collect the head, please.

00:07:52.889 --> 00:07:54.724 position:50% align:center
And then dispose of the body.

00:07:54.808 --> 00:07:56.142 position:50% align:center
[POLICEMAN D, E]
Hm!

00:07:56.226 --> 00:07:58.436 position:50% align:center
[INARI] Oh, and close
it up tight, okay?

00:07:58.520 --> 00:08:00.355 position:50% align:center
Otherwise, his body'll
grow back.

00:08:00.438 --> 00:08:02.315 position:50% align:center
[POLICEMAN D]
Yes, ma'am. Understood.

00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:04.359 position:50% align:center
[INARI]
Thank you!

00:08:04.442 --> 00:08:08.279 position:50% align:center
[INARI grunts]

00:08:08.363 --> 00:08:10.198 position:50% align:center
It's heavy!

00:08:10.281 --> 00:08:11.700 position:50% align:center
Let me carry it.

00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:13.326 position:50% align:center
You mean it?

00:08:13.410 --> 00:08:15.286 position:50% align:center
I so appreciate that!

00:08:15.370 --> 00:08:18.623 position:50% align:center
Well, you're kind of like a
mother to me, Lady Inari.

00:08:18.707 --> 00:08:20.625 position:50% align:center
If you're in trouble,
of course I'm gonna help.

00:08:20.709 --> 00:08:22.627 position:50% align:center
Aren't you just a sweetheart!

00:08:22.711 --> 00:08:24.129 position:50% align:center
Thank you!

00:08:24.212 --> 00:08:26.756 position:50% align:center
You really are a good girl, Kon.

00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:28.466 position:50% align:center
Good girl?

00:08:31.845 --> 00:08:33.096 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.265 position:50% align:center
If I can mass produce these,
then we'll no longer

00:08:35.348 --> 00:08:39.019 position:50% align:center
have to suffer the tedium
of co-existing with humans.

00:08:39.102 --> 00:08:41.479 position:50% align:center
Deliver the head up
to my room later.

00:08:41.563 --> 00:08:46.026 position:50% align:center
I'm going out now to do some
investigating on this lifestone.

00:08:46.109 --> 00:08:47.193 position:50% align:center
Oops!

00:08:47.277 --> 00:08:50.363 position:50% align:center
Ah, yes, I almost forgot.

00:08:50.447 --> 00:08:51.781 position:50% align:center
He's not alone.

00:08:51.865 --> 00:08:54.868 position:50% align:center
Kabane came with
some friends, right?

00:08:54.951 --> 00:08:56.369 position:50% align:center
Go and take care of them.

00:08:56.453 --> 00:08:57.746 position:50% align:center
Please, Kon?

00:08:57.829 --> 00:08:59.039 position:50% align:center
[KON]
Mm!

00:08:59.122 --> 00:09:02.459 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI grunt, growls]

00:09:02.542 --> 00:09:04.919 position:50% align:center
This is the worst!
I hate waiting.

00:09:05.003 --> 00:09:06.880 position:50% align:center
It's exactly why I didn't
wanna come here!

00:09:06.963 --> 00:09:08.465 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA giggles]

00:09:08.548 --> 00:09:10.550 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Shiki, check it out!

00:09:10.633 --> 00:09:12.344 position:50% align:center
Looks cute, huh?

00:09:15.221 --> 00:09:18.016 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] Did you tag along
just for clout?

00:09:18.099 --> 00:09:19.559 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Sorry to keep you.

00:09:22.312 --> 00:09:24.314 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] Well, it sure
took you long enough!

00:09:24.397 --> 00:09:26.232 position:50% align:center
You know how many hours
we've been waiting?

00:09:26.316 --> 00:09:28.026 position:50% align:center
It's been 30 minutes.

00:09:28.109 --> 00:09:31.154 position:50% align:center
So, Kabane. What've you
got in that case, there?

00:09:31.237 --> 00:09:32.739 position:50% align:center
It's not mine.

00:09:32.822 --> 00:09:35.658 position:50% align:center
I have to deliver it
up to the room later.

00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:37.577 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
You mean Inugami's room?

00:09:37.660 --> 00:09:38.661 position:50% align:center
No, Lady Inari's.

00:09:38.745 --> 00:09:40.955 position:50% align:center
Ew! Did you say Lady Inari?

00:09:41.039 --> 00:09:44.542 position:50% align:center
Hey, no offense. But you seem
kinda different, Kabane.

00:09:44.626 --> 00:09:46.753 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Gross. Never say that again.

00:09:46.836 --> 00:09:48.004 position:50% align:center
So what's wrong with you?

00:09:48.088 --> 00:09:51.132 position:50% align:center
Did that kitsune biddy
bait you with something?

00:09:51.216 --> 00:09:54.302 position:50% align:center
Take that back. She's no biddy!

00:09:55.762 --> 00:09:58.223 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI, AKIRA gasps]

00:09:58.306 --> 00:10:00.934 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Shiki! Kabane is...!

00:10:01.017 --> 00:10:03.853 position:50% align:center
[KON gasps]
That's a big "oops".

00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:05.897 position:50% align:center
And Lady Inari
asked me so nicely.

00:10:05.980 --> 00:10:07.440 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA gasps]

00:10:07.524 --> 00:10:08.817 position:50% align:center
[KON]
It's too late.

00:10:10.276 --> 00:10:11.778 position:50% align:center
Now die.

00:10:22.288 --> 00:10:23.832 position:50% align:center
It's that girl from earlier!

00:10:23.915 --> 00:10:25.875 position:50% align:center
So you're a kitsune, too!

00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:27.419 position:50% align:center
Where is Kabane?

00:10:30.463 --> 00:10:32.924 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA, SHIKI shout]

00:10:33.008 --> 00:10:34.968 position:50% align:center
[shouting continues]

00:10:38.304 --> 00:10:39.931 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA gasps]

00:10:40.015 --> 00:10:41.599 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
What do you think you're doing?

00:10:41.683 --> 00:10:43.351 position:50% align:center
You can't just start a fire!

00:10:43.435 --> 00:10:45.145 position:50% align:center
There are innocent people here!

00:10:45.228 --> 00:10:47.605 position:50% align:center
Heh. That's not a big deal.

00:10:47.689 --> 00:10:50.108 position:50% align:center
The police belong to Lady Inari.

00:10:50.191 --> 00:10:52.527 position:50% align:center
Any person who sets
foot in this building,

00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:55.405 position:50% align:center
automatically becomes
entranced by her.

00:10:55.488 --> 00:10:58.199 position:50% align:center
They think nothing.
They feel nothing.

00:10:58.283 --> 00:11:00.827 position:50% align:center
They're just puppets
doing their jobs.

00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:03.079 position:50% align:center
And they don't feel pain.

00:11:03.163 --> 00:11:04.914 position:50% align:center
Typical kitsune illusions.

00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:07.083 position:50% align:center
I really freaking
hate that old witch!

00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:09.294 position:50% align:center
How you dare insult Lady Inari!

00:11:09.377 --> 00:11:12.964 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA whimpers]

00:11:13.048 --> 00:11:14.632 position:50% align:center
It's no use trying to run.

00:11:14.716 --> 00:11:16.968 position:50% align:center
I'm not gonna fail,
cause I'm a good girl.

00:11:17.052 --> 00:11:19.220 position:50% align:center
And that means I'll
kill you no matter what.

00:11:19.304 --> 00:11:22.432 position:50% align:center
Well. Get ready for a fight!

00:11:22.515 --> 00:11:24.684 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI grunts]

00:11:24.768 --> 00:11:28.313 position:50% align:center
It's no use, Shiki, we gotta get
outta here before she kills us!

00:11:28.396 --> 00:11:30.190 position:50% align:center
You could always
try helping, dummy!

00:11:30.273 --> 00:11:31.691 position:50% align:center
I can't!

00:11:31.775 --> 00:11:33.026 position:50% align:center
Give up now.

00:11:33.109 --> 00:11:34.903 position:50% align:center
'Cause there's not a
chance you'll survive this. 

00:11:34.986 --> 00:11:38.823 position:50% align:center
Is that right?
Okay then, what if I do this?

00:11:38.907 --> 00:11:40.116 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:41.618 --> 00:11:42.702 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI grunts]

00:11:42.786 --> 00:11:45.205 position:50% align:center
So you have to bring
this to Lady Inari.

00:11:45.288 --> 00:11:47.332 position:50% align:center
Bet you're up a creek if
someone takes it, huh?

00:11:47.415 --> 00:11:48.708 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:11:48.792 --> 00:11:51.336 position:50% align:center
Awesome! I never even saw
you shoot your silk out!

00:11:51.419 --> 00:11:54.047 position:50% align:center
I couldn't very well do it when
she would notice, right?

00:11:54.130 --> 00:11:56.925 position:50% align:center
Now, let's see what
she has in here.

00:11:57.008 --> 00:11:57.842 position:50% align:center
Hi.

00:11:57.926 --> 00:11:59.594 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI shouts]
What the--?!

00:11:59.678 --> 00:12:01.888 position:50% align:center
What am I even looking at?

00:12:04.349 --> 00:12:07.686 position:50% align:center
But how? How'd he
take the head away?

00:12:07.769 --> 00:12:09.270 position:50% align:center
Why me?

00:12:09.354 --> 00:12:10.647 position:50% align:center
Thank you!

00:12:10.730 --> 00:12:13.650 position:50% align:center
You really are a good girl, Kon.

00:12:13.733 --> 00:12:16.152 position:50% align:center
Good girl?

00:12:16.236 --> 00:12:19.572 position:50% align:center
[KON] I won't... be a
good girl anymore.

00:12:19.656 --> 00:12:21.074 position:50% align:center
I won't...

00:12:23.243 --> 00:12:24.619 position:50% align:center
Give it back!

00:12:26.204 --> 00:12:27.539 position:50% align:center
[KON]
They're gone!

00:12:27.622 --> 00:12:30.041 position:50% align:center
Where are you?!

00:12:30.125 --> 00:12:32.419 position:50% align:center
Where did you go?!

00:12:32.502 --> 00:12:35.964 position:50% align:center
[KON grunts]
Come out, you cowards!

00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:40.927 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI grunts]

00:12:41.011 --> 00:12:43.680 position:50% align:center
Show yourselves! Come out, now!

00:12:45.181 --> 00:12:47.392 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
You rescued me. Thanks.

00:12:47.475 --> 00:12:49.394 position:50% align:center
I had assumed my body
would never grow back,

00:12:49.477 --> 00:12:50.770 position:50% align:center
with my head locked
up like that.

00:12:50.854 --> 00:12:52.439 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
We don't have time to be mushy!

00:12:52.522 --> 00:12:53.982 position:50% align:center
The hell is going on, anyway?

00:12:54.065 --> 00:12:56.693 position:50% align:center
That girl was delivering
your head to Inari.

00:12:56.776 --> 00:12:59.487 position:50% align:center
I don't know what this is about,
but it can't be good!

00:12:59.571 --> 00:13:01.072 position:50% align:center
Akira, wake up!

00:13:01.156 --> 00:13:03.783 position:50% align:center
We've got Kabane, so now we need
to report back and let Inugami 

00:13:03.867 --> 00:13:04.826 position:50% align:center
know what's going down!

00:13:04.909 --> 00:13:06.411 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Shiki.

00:13:06.494 --> 00:13:08.705 position:50% align:center
Would you stop talking to me?
It's the creepiest thing ever!

00:13:08.788 --> 00:13:11.207 position:50% align:center
[KABANE] I know what's
happening, more or less.

00:13:11.291 --> 00:13:13.543 position:50% align:center
When the timing's right,
throw me at her.

00:13:13.626 --> 00:13:14.794 position:50% align:center
I'll take her down.

00:13:14.878 --> 00:13:16.504 position:50% align:center
Seriously? You're a head!

00:13:16.588 --> 00:13:18.715 position:50% align:center
What do you think you're
gonna do, you freakin weirdo?

00:13:18.798 --> 00:13:20.050 position:50% align:center
Trust me.

00:13:20.133 --> 00:13:21.760 position:50% align:center
Where the hell do you
get this confidence from?

00:13:21.843 --> 00:13:23.845 position:50% align:center
You're literally just a
"thing" right now!

00:13:23.928 --> 00:13:26.348 position:50% align:center
Shiki, line up the
shot and I can do it.

00:13:26.431 --> 00:13:27.724 position:50% align:center
Have faith.

00:13:27.807 --> 00:13:29.309 position:50% align:center
Are you kidding me?

00:13:34.064 --> 00:13:38.735 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] Well... Knowing him,
he might be able to pull it off.

00:13:38.818 --> 00:13:40.779 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Just throw me. I've got this.

00:13:40.862 --> 00:13:42.614 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI gasps]

00:13:42.697 --> 00:13:45.158 position:50% align:center
[KON grunts]

00:13:47.369 --> 00:13:48.578 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Hey!

00:13:50.163 --> 00:13:52.540 position:50% align:center
[growls]
Give it back!

00:13:52.624 --> 00:13:55.043 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Don't blame me, alright?

00:13:55.126 --> 00:13:56.378 position:50% align:center
[KON shouts]

00:14:02.300 --> 00:14:03.551 position:50% align:center
Kabane!

00:14:06.346 --> 00:14:07.555 position:50% align:center
Pretty good.

00:14:08.807 --> 00:14:10.684 position:50% align:center
Ugh. Gross.

00:14:10.767 --> 00:14:12.560 position:50% align:center
Sorry, I guess I messed up.

00:14:12.644 --> 00:14:14.104 position:50% align:center
I was trying to bite
a chunk out of her.

00:14:14.187 --> 00:14:15.730 position:50% align:center
Would you stop talking?

00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:18.525 position:50% align:center
I am never doing this again,
you understand?

00:14:20.485 --> 00:14:24.489 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] The fire.
Everything's back to normal!

00:14:24.572 --> 00:14:28.618 position:50% align:center
[snores]

00:14:28.702 --> 00:14:30.745 position:50% align:center
It was an illusion.

00:14:30.829 --> 00:14:33.373 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:14:35.583 --> 00:14:37.877 position:50% align:center
Shiki. Give me a little room.

00:14:37.961 --> 00:14:39.921 position:50% align:center
Um... Okay.

00:14:40.005 --> 00:14:41.297 position:50% align:center
[KABANE exhales]

00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:44.509 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:47.053 --> 00:14:48.638 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:14:55.311 --> 00:14:56.688 position:50% align:center
All better.

00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:00.859 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI, KABANE grunt]

00:15:00.942 --> 00:15:03.111 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
How?

00:15:03.194 --> 00:15:04.821 position:50% align:center
The things you can do.

00:15:04.904 --> 00:15:06.031 position:50% align:center
I know they're impossible,

00:15:06.114 --> 00:15:08.700 position:50% align:center
but somehow, you're still
able to do them!

00:15:10.452 --> 00:15:12.662 position:50% align:center
[sighs]
Put this on.

00:15:15.498 --> 00:15:17.334 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] You're really
getting on my nerves!

00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:19.002 position:50% align:center
Making me look like a chicken.

00:15:19.085 --> 00:15:22.964 position:50% align:center
But FYI, I stay rational
when faced with reality!

00:15:23.048 --> 00:15:24.382 position:50% align:center
So, there's no chance
that you're gonna

00:15:24.466 --> 00:15:25.884 position:50% align:center
rub off on me, 'kay?

00:15:25.967 --> 00:15:29.387 position:50% align:center
That's good. For my sake,
I'd rather you were rational.

00:15:29.471 --> 00:15:30.764 position:50% align:center
Well, great.

00:15:34.517 --> 00:15:35.769 position:50% align:center
Go on.

00:15:35.852 --> 00:15:37.520 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
Hm?

00:15:37.604 --> 00:15:40.023 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI sighs]

00:15:40.106 --> 00:15:41.649 position:50% align:center
Stick out your fist.

00:15:41.733 --> 00:15:44.944 position:50% align:center
It's something that buddies do
whenever they celebrate a win.

00:15:46.404 --> 00:15:48.782 position:50% align:center
They do, huh? All right.

00:15:52.619 --> 00:15:54.871 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Come on!

00:15:56.581 --> 00:15:58.833 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
His head! It was just...

00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:00.210 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Yo!

00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:01.336 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Oh, hey!

00:16:01.419 --> 00:16:02.545 position:50% align:center
From the looks of it,

00:16:02.629 --> 00:16:04.756 position:50% align:center
things went just about
the way I expected.

00:16:04.839 --> 00:16:07.008 position:50% align:center
You mean you knew
this would happen?

00:16:07.092 --> 00:16:10.428 position:50% align:center
If it came down to it,
I was planning on rushing in.

00:16:10.512 --> 00:16:12.097 position:50% align:center
But you're fine.

00:16:12.180 --> 00:16:13.556 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS giggle]

00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:17.227 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI] Let's get going.
The car's parked nearby.

00:16:17.310 --> 00:16:19.896 position:50% align:center
So Kabane, where's that
good-luck charm?

00:16:19.979 --> 00:16:20.980 position:50% align:center
[KABANE]
She took it from me.

00:16:21.064 --> 00:16:22.816 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Ha, I knew it.

00:16:30.198 --> 00:16:32.534 position:50% align:center
Oh, my adorable
little lifestone.

00:16:32.617 --> 00:16:35.578 position:50% align:center
I'm going to make a whole,
big family for you.

00:16:45.505 --> 00:16:46.381 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:16:46.464 --> 00:16:49.718 position:50% align:center
[phone rings]

00:16:52.804 --> 00:16:54.222 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Inari, hey.

00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:57.267 position:50% align:center
Inugami. You rotten...!

00:16:57.350 --> 00:17:00.103 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI] That was a pretty
terrible thing for you to do.

00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:03.857 position:50% align:center
In the end, my guys barely
escaped with their lives.

00:17:03.940 --> 00:17:06.276 position:50% align:center
And here I thought the two
of us were like blood

00:17:06.359 --> 00:17:08.069 position:50% align:center
after all these years.

00:17:08.153 --> 00:17:10.155 position:50% align:center
But you betrayed me.

00:17:10.238 --> 00:17:12.782 position:50% align:center
I guess that means
you owe me one now.

00:17:12.866 --> 00:17:14.200 position:50% align:center
What did you just say?

00:17:14.284 --> 00:17:16.036 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI] You must be
getting old if you can't see 

00:17:16.119 --> 00:17:17.704 position:50% align:center
through my shapeshifting.

00:17:17.787 --> 00:17:21.499 position:50% align:center
Are you really that
infatuated with lifestones?

00:17:21.583 --> 00:17:23.251 position:50% align:center
--[AKIRA gasps]
--[SHIKI gags] Gross!

00:17:23.335 --> 00:17:25.045 position:50% align:center
Where were you keeping that?

00:17:26.880 --> 00:17:30.425 position:50% align:center
It's too bad. That one
belongs to Kabane.

00:17:30.508 --> 00:17:33.595 position:50% align:center
Next time, you'll be
dealing with me. Got it?

00:17:33.678 --> 00:17:34.888 position:50% align:center
[phone hangs up]

00:17:38.850 --> 00:17:41.061 position:50% align:center
[MALE DRIVER A] Ma'am, we're
nearly at your destination.

00:17:41.144 --> 00:17:42.812 position:50% align:center
Where would you like to stop?

00:17:45.065 --> 00:17:49.611 position:50% align:center
[INARI yells]

00:17:49.694 --> 00:17:51.571 position:50% align:center
[MALE DRIVER A screams]

00:17:51.654 --> 00:17:54.324 position:50% align:center
[crashing]

00:17:54.407 --> 00:17:56.409 position:50% align:center
[MAN A]
Whoa! Did you see that?

00:17:56.493 --> 00:17:57.660 position:50% align:center
[GIRL C]
Call an ambulance!

00:17:57.744 --> 00:17:58.787 position:50% align:center
[MAN B]
What was that?

00:17:58.870 --> 00:18:01.081 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow. That's a bad accident!

00:18:01.164 --> 00:18:04.250 position:50% align:center
You're right,
looks pretty serious.

00:18:04.334 --> 00:18:09.089 position:50% align:center
[INARI] Aw, what a shame!
Guess I'll rest up at a café!

00:18:12.467 --> 00:18:14.469 position:50% align:center
Are you really sure about this?

00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:16.471 position:50% align:center
Going up against that old witch?

00:18:16.554 --> 00:18:18.682 position:50% align:center
She's someone with an
awful lot of influence

00:18:18.765 --> 00:18:20.183 position:50% align:center
with the police, isn't she?

00:18:20.266 --> 00:18:22.519 position:50% align:center
This really isn't that
big of a deal.

00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:24.688 position:50% align:center
It's kind of like we're
negotiating the boundaries

00:18:24.771 --> 00:18:27.440 position:50% align:center
between our two territories,
that's all.

00:18:27.524 --> 00:18:30.193 position:50% align:center
You'll understand more
once you're adults.

00:18:30.276 --> 00:18:32.696 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Once we're adults?

00:18:32.779 --> 00:18:35.365 position:50% align:center
Never mind, whaddaya say
we grab some grub?

00:18:35.448 --> 00:18:37.701 position:50% align:center
A welcome party for Kabane, eh?

00:18:37.784 --> 00:18:39.077 position:50% align:center
Oh, sounds like fun!

00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:40.245 position:50% align:center
Let's do it!

00:18:40.328 --> 00:18:42.038 position:50% align:center
I'm in the mood for
Chinese food today!

00:18:42.122 --> 00:18:43.540 position:50% align:center
I want pancakes!

00:18:43.623 --> 00:18:45.875 position:50% align:center
Don't be stupid!
We're talking about dinner!

00:18:45.959 --> 00:18:46.751 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
So what?

00:18:46.835 --> 00:18:47.919 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
That's not dinner!

00:18:48.003 --> 00:18:49.421 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Kabane, which would you like?

00:18:49.504 --> 00:18:52.716 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI] How'll that fill
you up? Chinese, or else!

00:18:52.799 --> 00:18:53.925 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA]
Pancakes!

00:18:54.009 --> 00:18:55.593 position:50% align:center
[BOTH growl]

00:18:55.677 --> 00:18:57.387 position:50% align:center
--How about both?
--Huh?

00:18:57.470 --> 00:18:59.055 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI laughs]

00:18:59.139 --> 00:19:00.724 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI]
Are you serious?

00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:07.355 position:50% align:center
[KON pants]

00:19:13.528 --> 00:19:16.740 position:50% align:center
I'm a good girl. I am.

00:19:16.823 --> 00:19:21.327 position:50% align:center
I'll... deliver... his head now.

00:19:23.371 --> 00:19:26.374 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI] Hey. Lookin kinda
rough back there!

00:19:26.458 --> 00:19:27.751 position:50% align:center
Ugh.

00:19:27.834 --> 00:19:31.838 position:50% align:center
Greasy stuff, plus sweet
stuff isn't a good combo.

00:19:31.921 --> 00:19:34.591 position:50% align:center
[AKIRA] Yeah. I ate
too much of it, too.

00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:36.760 position:50% align:center
That wasn't smart.

00:19:36.843 --> 00:19:38.345 position:50% align:center
You're okay, though, yeah?

00:19:38.428 --> 00:19:39.971 position:50% align:center
Sure am.

00:19:40.055 --> 00:19:42.140 position:50% align:center
Steady as a rock, huh?

00:19:42.223 --> 00:19:44.893 position:50% align:center
Oh, right. I guess
I'd better explain

00:19:44.976 --> 00:19:47.854 position:50% align:center
how we're able to
bring in the business.

00:19:47.937 --> 00:19:50.190 position:50% align:center
There are web searches and
word-of-mouth and things

00:19:50.273 --> 00:19:52.650 position:50% align:center
like that, of course.

00:19:52.734 --> 00:19:56.029 position:50% align:center
But beyond that,
there's our signage.

00:19:56.112 --> 00:19:58.448 position:50% align:center
This light attracts kemono.

00:19:58.531 --> 00:20:01.868 position:50% align:center
It also attracts humans who
have been empowered by kemono.

00:20:01.951 --> 00:20:05.372 position:50% align:center
Which means that our
work naturally finds us.

00:20:05.455 --> 00:20:08.291 position:50% align:center
Incidentally, Inari is the
one who whipped this up.

00:20:08.375 --> 00:20:10.794 position:50% align:center
So, wait, is she on
our side, or not?

00:20:10.877 --> 00:20:14.005 position:50% align:center
It's more of a collaborative
relationship, I'd say.

00:20:14.089 --> 00:20:15.757 position:50% align:center
[KON grunts]

00:20:18.635 --> 00:20:20.679 position:50% align:center
It's the kitsune
girl from today!

00:20:20.762 --> 00:20:22.555 position:50% align:center
You mean she followed us?

00:20:22.639 --> 00:20:25.141 position:50% align:center
I'm... a good girl.

00:20:25.225 --> 00:20:27.477 position:50% align:center
I need... his head!

00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:28.478 position:50% align:center
[SHIKI, AKIRA gasp]

00:20:28.561 --> 00:20:32.148 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:20:32.232 --> 00:20:34.442 position:50% align:center
Uh. What just happened?

00:20:34.526 --> 00:20:35.819 position:50% align:center
Is she dead?

00:20:35.902 --> 00:20:37.987 position:50% align:center
No way.

00:20:38.071 --> 00:20:40.907 position:50% align:center
[stomach growls]

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:42.033 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:20:42.117 --> 00:20:46.913 position:50% align:center
[KON munches]

00:20:51.292 --> 00:20:52.669 position:50% align:center
Let me get this straight.

00:20:52.752 --> 00:20:54.587 position:50% align:center
All you want is Kabane's head?

00:20:54.671 --> 00:20:55.797 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's right.

00:20:55.880 --> 00:20:57.298 position:50% align:center
'Cause I'm a good girl,

00:20:57.382 --> 00:20:59.467 position:50% align:center
and that means I'll never quit
my mission midway through.

00:20:59.551 --> 00:21:01.219 position:50% align:center
[INUGAMI]
Mm-hm...

00:21:04.097 --> 00:21:06.224 position:50% align:center
[KON grunts]
The head!

00:21:06.307 --> 00:21:08.810 position:50% align:center
Okay, slow your
roll there, kiddo!

00:21:08.893 --> 00:21:10.395 position:50% align:center
This chick is bad news!

00:21:10.478 --> 00:21:13.273 position:50% align:center
C'mon, let's take
her down, Inugami!

00:21:13.356 --> 00:21:16.317 position:50% align:center
We will not be taking
anyone down, ya hear.

00:21:17.944 --> 00:21:19.529 position:50% align:center
Someone who stands
on top of tables

00:21:19.612 --> 00:21:21.364 position:50% align:center
doesn't have very good manners.

00:21:21.448 --> 00:21:22.949 position:50% align:center
Inari would be disappointed.

00:21:23.033 --> 00:21:24.242 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:21:30.749 --> 00:21:34.336 position:50% align:center
You say "thank you"
after you eat, dontcha?

00:21:34.419 --> 00:21:36.546 position:50% align:center
[KON]
Yes... Thank you.

00:21:36.629 --> 00:21:39.591 position:50% align:center
And you also clean up
after yourself.

00:21:39.674 --> 00:21:41.176 position:50% align:center
[KON]
All right...

00:21:41.259 --> 00:21:42.844 position:50% align:center
That's for the regular trash.

00:21:42.927 --> 00:21:44.596 position:50% align:center
And this is recyclables.

00:21:44.679 --> 00:21:46.056 position:50% align:center
[KON]
Understood.

